'''''White Shadow''''' is a 2013 internationally co-produced [[drama film]] written, produced and directed by Noaz Deshe.<ref>{{cite web |title=Noaz Deshe on his Film, White Shadow: A Fight for Survival in East Africa|url=http://www.internationalpolicydigest.org/2014/01/24/noaz-deshe-on-his-film-white-shadow-a-fight-for-survival-in-east-africa/|accessdate=April 14, 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=Sundance Interview with Noaz Deshe, director of White Shadow|url=http://cltampa.com/artbreaker/archives/2014/01/27/sundance-interview-with-noaz-deshe-director-of-white-shadow|accessdate=April 14, 2014}}</ref> An [[international co-production]] between [[Germany]], [[Italy]] and [[Tanzania]], the film premiered in ''Critics’ Week selection'' at the [[70th Venice International Film Festival]] on September 2, 2013. It won the ''Lion of the future'' award at the festival.<ref name="a">{{cite web |title=70th Venice Film Festival Award Winners: Gianfranco Rosi’s SACRO GRA, Tye Sheridan for David Gordon Green’s JOE & Gabe Klinger’s DOUBLE PLAY Doc|url=http://collider.com/venice-film-festival-award-winners/|accessdate=April 14, 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=The 70th Venice Film Festival is a Historic Mess -- and Still a Thing of Beauty|url=http://www.indiewire.com/article/the-70th-venice-film-festival-is-a-historic-mess-and-still-a-thing-of-beauty|accessdate=April 14, 2014}}</ref>	

The film later premiered in-competition in the ''World Cinema Dramatic Competition'' at [[2014 Sundance Film Festival]] on January 17, 2014.<ref>{{cite web |title=Sundance 2014: World Cinema Dramatic Competition|url=http://www.indiewire.com/article/sundance-2014-world-cinema-dramatic-competition|accessdate=January 18, 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=Sundance trailer of the day: ‘White Shadow’ [video]|url=http://www.sltrib.com/sltrib/blogssundanceblog/57322731-50/sundance-festival-shadow-2014.html.csp|accessdate=January 18, 2014}}</ref> The film also screened at 2014 [[San Francisco International Film Festival]] on May 4, 2014.<ref>{{cite web |title=12 Must-See Films and One We Defy You to Sit Through at the SFIFF|url=http://ww2.kqed.org/arts/2014/04/21/a-handy-guide-to-the-2014-san-francisco-international-film-festival/|accessdate=January 18, 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=Every San Franciscan's Guide to the San Francisco International Film Festival|url=http://www.modernluxury.com/san-francisco/story/every-san-franciscans-guide-the-san-francisco-international-film-festival|accessdate=January 18, 2014}}</ref> [[Ryan Gosling]] along with [[Matteo Ceccarini]] and [[Eva Riccobono]] served as the executive producers of the film.<ref>{{cite web |title=Venice 2013 Critic’s Notebook: A Means of Escape — African Cinema on the Lido.|url=http://filmmakermagazine.com/76061-venice-2013-critics-notebook-a-means-of-escape-african-cinema-on-the-lido/|accessdate=January 18, 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.latimes.com/entertainment/lat-venice-2013-wre0011066167-20130827,0,924030.photo|title=Matteo Ceccarini LATimes|date=2013}}</ref>

==Plot==
Alias, a young [[Albinism|Albino]], is on the run from the local doctors, who are hunting Albinos to use their body parts for potions.

==Cast==
*Hamisi Bazili as Alias
*James Gayo as Kosmos
*Glory Mbayuwayu as Antoinette
*Salum Abdallah as Salum
*Riziki Ally as Mother
*John S. Mwakipunda as Anulla
*Tito D. Ntanga	as Father
*James P. Salala as Adin

==Reception==
''White Shadow'' received mostly positive reviews from critics. Guy Lodge of ''[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]'', said in his review that "Noaz Deshe makes a staggering debut with this drama about the African albino multi trade."<ref>{{cite web |title=Sundance Film Review: ‘White Shadow’|url=https://variety.com/2014/film/reviews/sundance-film-review-white-shadow-1201081482/|accessdate=April 14, 2014}}</ref> Boyd van Hoeij in his review for ''[[The Hollywood Reporter]]'' said that "This harrowing account of a young albino's fight for survival in Tanzania is too long but nonetheless often gripping."<ref>{{cite web |title=White Shadow: Sundance Review|url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/review/white-shadow-sundance-review-672074|accessdate=April 14, 2014}}</ref> Jessica Kiang of ''[[Indiewire]]'' grade the film B+ and praised the film by saying that "We have to admit, it first took a lot of our patience, and then all of our nerve, to make it through to the end, but that simply makes it a film that is exactly as upsetting as its subject matter warrants."<ref>{{cite web |title=Sundance Review: Noaz Deshe's Disturbing, Distressing Venice Winner 'White Shadow'|url=http://blogs.indiewire.com/theplaylist/sundance-review-noaz-deshes-disturbing-distressing-venice-winner-white-shadow-20140118|accessdate=April 14, 2014}}</ref>

